               <p>MARSHALL ROBINSON, ESQ. On the 17th of June, about one o'clock in the day, I was walking in <placeName id="t18190707-19-crimeloc110">Bedford-square</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18190707-19-crimeloc110" type="placeName" value="Bedford-square"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18190707-19-crimeloc110" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190707-19-off107 t18190707-19-crimeloc110"></join>, felt something pull my coat behind, turned round, and charged the prisoner with picking my pocket - he had his hand behind his back - I took hold of him, and he instantly gave me my handkerchief, said he was very sorry, but he did it from distress, and if I would let him go he would never do so again; two others were with him, who went off. I took him to Marlborough-street.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. Two men were following the gentleman, one of them threw the handkerchief over his shoulder, and I picked it up.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18190707-19-verdict111" type="verdictDescription">
